Stephanie Mills (born around 1969) was a character on the 1970s American television situation comedy All in the Family and the follow-up series Archie Bunker's Place.
She was portrayed by child actress Danielle Brisebois, who joined All in the Family in 1978.
Brisebois continued in the role until Archie Bunker's Place ended its run in 1983.

In the latter years of Archie Bunker's Place, Stephanie would be one of two teenaged girls living under Archie's roof, the other being Archie's 18-year-old niece Barbara Lee "Billie" Bunker (portrayed by Denise Miller).
